Knowledge of eliciting requirements from interviews with customers;
Knowledge of writing system requirements documents based on the interviews;
Knowledge of leading a complete and detailed analysis of business processes;
Knowledge of software development life cycle methodology;
Knowledge of software change control processes;
Knowledge of structured query language;
Knowledge of software development life cycle and systems development life cycle concepts;
Knowledge of business and management principles involved in strategic planning, resource allocation, leadership technique, production methods, and coordination of people and resources;
Knowledge project management principles and practices;
Skill in the use of MS Word, Excel, and Outlook;
Skill in gathering, developing, documenting, and testing user requirements for systems and contracts to produce timely and high-quality requirements-related work products.
Skill in supporting development functions, including the contract solicitation and implementation, and providing subject matter expertise to ensure contracts are written to meet business objectives;
Skill in support operations agile development efforts, such as a Product Owner or Product Lead;
Skill in analyzing existing business processes, tools, and contracts and identifying opportunities for improvement;
Skill in conducting research for operations and presenting findings;
Skill in documenting or creating business processes;
Skill in using standard office software and equipment;
Skill in performing business or systems analysis using a defined methodology;
Skill in using a personal computer in a Windows environment and Microsoft software;
Skill in identifying and analyzing resources needed and actions to be taken to ensure division needs are met with a quality product;
Skill in collaboration and problem solving;
Skill in basic mathematical computations;
Skill in handling multiple tasks, prioritizing, and effectively meeting deadlines;
Skill in exercising sound judgment and effective decision making;
